name: Teras
review: A unique and interesting island located in the middle of the Mahakam River right in the center of Tengarong and Tengarong Seberang, Kutai Kerta Negara Regency is called Kumala Island or Kumala Fantasy Island. What's interesting is that this island is specially designed as a tourist attraction typical of Dayak culture, which is beautiful and unique, combined with parks and green trees combined with Dayak reliefs. There are tall and multi-story betang houses made from native Kalimantan wood, namely ironwood. There is a hall provided on certain days for Dayak cultural performances, music and arts. There are also swimming pools, fountains and villas with good road facilities. There is a unique and distinctive Dayak souvenir center with a relatively complete variety. The island is relatively large. To surround this island there are Delmans or horses pulling wheeled carriages.

name: Agus Sunaryo
review:
The Repo - Repo Bridge is a link between the Tenggarong mainland and Kumala Island, which is located in the middle of the Mahakam River. This bridge was built in 2014 - 2016 with a length of 230m and a width of 3.5m, making this bridge specifically for pedestrians only.

In the¬†Kutai language "Repo-Repo" means padlock.¬†On this bridge, people can put repo-repos or padlocks with their names on the bridge railing as a keepsake or symbol of love.

We can cross this bridge (free) to go to Kumala Island in the middle of the Mahakam river, there are many family recreation facilities, places to eat and hang out or just relax and enjoy the view of the river and in the distance you can also see the Kutai Kartanegara Bridge from here.

TOP!!

name: Firda Norma Alida
review: Tourist attractions that families must visit. Lots of unique spots that are cool for photos. The area is very wide. But don't worry, there are vehicle rental services (bikes and electric motorbikes). Many sell food and souvenirs too. Anyway, good place. The downside is that during the day the sun here is really hot.
stars.label: 5 stars

name: yopie franz
review:
This was the last destination we visited from a series of other tourist attractions in Tenggarong.

I thought it would be normal. It turns out that if you go out with friends it will be more fun here. Apart from of course if you bring your family.

Feel the sensation of walking on a bridge which sometimes sways slightly due to the wind.

You can take photos or record videos while on the bridge. Or take a photo of this bridge before crossing and from the direction of Kumala Island.

There is a paid entry ticket to the bridge. Cheap, only Rp. 7000/person.

Oh yes, there are lots of padlocks on this bridge. It seems like there is some sort of custom for young couples to put a padlock with their names on it here.

Nice bridge to see.

Recommended.
stars.label: 5 stars

name: Titik Setyawati
review:
How many times have you been here, it's always exciting, there is lots of transportation that can be rented here to explore all the places on this small island, there are bicycles, electric scooters, carriages, mini trains and many others, just choose which one with different rental fees. Yes, just adjust it to your budget.
It's just that the island is not well maintained in terms of cleanliness because it was closed some time ago. If you come here, make sure you bring food or drink because there's nothing to sell inside, so make sure before crossing the pedestrian bridge, look for supplies first üòÅüòÅüòÅ
But there aren't many photos when you come here, because it's always when your cellphone drops üò¢üò¢üò¢
So just enjoy the tour fully

review: Bridge crossing to Kumala Island. In December 2022, it was being renovated and repainted. The view is quite good... Hopefully this Kumala island will be developed again and re-powered, it will be managed better so that it becomes the main destination again when you go to Tenggarong. Apart from being a source of regional income, it could become a center for cultural and educational tourism, especially in East Kalimantan.

name: Tara Andria
review:
Historic and iconic tourist attractions in Kutai Kartanegara Regency. When you board a plane, Kumala Island is very striking and is a sign that we are near the destination airport üòÅ
The parking area for motorbikes and cars is spacious, the parking attendants are friendly. There are many food and drink vendors, no need to be afraid of being hungry. When the sun is hot, there is also an umbrella rental service. To get to Kumala Island itself, we have to walk across the iconic Repo Repo Bridge. It is quite far, so make sure to wear comfortable shoes and clothes. The entrance ticket is priced at 7000 per person. Inside there are electric motorbikes, bicycles for rent, and there is also an odong odong train that can be used to go around Kumala Island. Actually, this island is very beautiful, and has a lot of potential, but unfortunately the maintenance is not optimal. If it is not maintained and left to deteriorate, it would be a shame. Please ask the local government to pay attention to this, so that it can compete with other regional specialties.

The photos produced here are definitely good, especially the combination of the river, clouds, and trees across it add to the beautiful scenery of the Repo-Repo Bridge.

name: Dewi Annisa Mamaraffiyya
review: A good and sturdy bridge and a bridge that can make people healthy, a bridge that connects Tenggarong city directly to Kumala Island by crossing on foot so that tourists can enjoy the beauty of Tenggarong city and can see the Mahakam river directly via this repo-repo bridge. Repo repo in Kutai language means key / padlock where you can put a love lock there, let's explore the city of Tenggarong and you have to stop by this repo repo bridge to continue exploring Kumala Island. Don't forget to bring a love padlock for young couples who want to immortalize their love on this bridge.

name: AFI DJ
review: Remember, it was still in 2007, the Tenggarong bridge was still standing solidly with the yellow color behind it. It looks really dirty from home. Here is another photo looking at the lembuswana statue. It's really big, my mother told me that this statue can fly because it has a mystical impression. Behind that, now it's really modern, lots of facilities have been built and it's cooler. Lots of good photo spots. And you can come here to refresh while discovering history because there is a museum of relics from the Kutai Kartanegara kingdom. It seems haunted but those who really like history can immediately come to Kumala Island in Tenggarong. In the past, access was fast. From Samarinda, you can cross directly on the Tenggarong bridge. Are you using boat access now? It's been a long time since I've been to Tenggaron. From Tenggarong to Kumala Island, take the Etek Etek boat, it only fits a few people. Don't be afraid, just enjoy it, the journey is a bit long. But it's really nice and beautiful.

name: Jol Shawabi
review:
Previously, when I went there in 2007, Kumala Island in Timbau, Tenggarong was really exciting. The rides there function well, and the historical heritage is well maintained.

But unfortunately, when I returned in 2021, the condition had changed drastically. Many of the rides are broken and no one seems to be taking care of them. It seems like the government or the budget doesn't really care.

In fact, Kumala Island could be an important source of income for the region. Come on, let's speak out and encourage Kumala Island to rise again! Everyone can join in, and we can make this place like it was before. :) üí™üèùÔ∏è #SaveKumalaPulau

name: Jamaludin
review:
The Kumala Island tourist attraction, which is located in the middle of the Mahakam River, is a recreation park that combines modern technology and traditional culture. This 76 hectare island was once a wasteland and bushes. Currently, some areas are equipped with various facilities such as a 100 meter high sky tower to enjoy the beauty from the air, a mini railway play area and a cable car that connects to the mainland.

On this island there is a DSJ Resort complete with a swimming pool and facilities for those who want to rest, namely the only cottage in the middle of the Mahakam River. At this island location there is a giant aquarium for porpoises, freshwater dolphins which only exist in the People's Republic of China and Brazil.

The construction of the Kumala Island Tourist Park is being carried out in stages and will continue to develop. In this way, the public will get additional representative tourist attractions besides the Mulawarman Museum (former palace of the Kutai Kartanegara Kingdom), Panji Sukarame Reservoir, Pondok Labu Cultural Village in Tenggarong and Nusa Tuna in Muara Muntai District which has white sand.

Kumala Island Tourist Park is around 27 km from Samarinda City which can be reached via the Kutai Kartanegara Bridge in approximately 30 minutes. Meanwhile, from Balikpapan City, which has Sultan Aji Muhammad Sulaiman Airport facilities and Semayang Harbor, which is access to air and sea transportation in East Kalimantan, the distance is around 130 km which can be reached in approximately 3 hours by road. Apart from that, Kumala Island Tourist Park can also be reached by water transportation via the Mahakam River.

name: Marwan Mohamad
review: Kumala Island is an island located in the middle of the Mahakam River in front of Tenggarong City. This island was previously left alone before being managed to become one of the mainstay tourist destinations in Kutai Kertanegara Regency. There are many interesting rides on this island such as a train to get around the island, the Lembuswana monument, a cable car from the island to Tenggarong Seberang. There is also a Sky Tower which we can climb to see the view of Tenggarong City from above.
